revision.text:
{{Commons category|Agglutinative languages}}
{{Cat main|Agglutinative language}}
Articles relating to [[agglutinative language]]s, a type of [[synthetic language]] with morphology that primarily uses [[agglutination]]. Words may contain different [[morpheme]]s to determine their meanings, but all of these morphemes (including [[word stem|stem]]s and [[affix]]es) remain, in every aspect, unchanged after their unions.
{{CatAutoTOC}}

[[Category:Synthetic languages]]

